	India finish 4th  
	Calcutta: Brazil successfully defended their World Championship title defeating Cuba 3-2 (30-28, 21-25, 25-22, 23-25, 15-8) while India lost 0-3 (19-25, 16-25, 22-25) to Argentina and finished fourth in the FIVB Men rsquo;s U-21 Volleyball World Championship in Pune on Sunday.     
	Terrassa (Spain): India lost 2-8 to Spain in their first hockey Test. The Spaniards made five goals in the first half before adding three more in the second session to complete the rout. India rsquo;s consolation goals were scored by Hari Prasad in the 51st minute and the second by Rajpal Singh.    
	New Delhi: Injured hockey goalkeeper Baljit Singh is confident of getting his full vision back and returning to the field after an eye operation in a private hospital at Alabama on Tuesday.
      
	New Delhi: India made a fine start at the Asian Zone 3.2 World Cup Qualifying Chess Championship with Grandmasters Praveen Thipsay and Neelotpal Das clinching easy wins in their first-round matches on Sunday.
      
